args:
The prince and friends defeat the fiends with the
aid of Lucretia, but this does not help the town
rest much easier. Meanwhile, a mysterious
shadow continues whispering to Elias, and its
influence may be causing the fiends to grow
even stronger...
I don't think these guys are gonna stop\nanytime soon. We may need to pull back.
Good heavens, but there ARE quite a\nfew of them here, aren't there?
Well, isn't that sweet! But you don't need\nto worry about me.
Holy crap! I thought this lady was\nsupposed to be some famous singer,\nnot some famous fiendslayer!
Oh, I am a famous singer! ...That said,\nI do like to dabble in arts of the more\n＂martial＂ variety.
I'd call that a little more than dabblin'.
Either way, we appreciate your help.
You're quite welcome. Honestly, the only\nthing that matters is seeing everyone safe.
Ah, my dear Vixel. Is something\nthe matter? You're all in a dither.
You vanished without a trace earlier,\nand now I find you here!
Wait, that's Pia! Why is SHE here?!
And I wanted to stop her, but I was so\nscared that I couldn't talk!
Easy on the waterworks, now.\nThe fiends are all gone.
*sniff* I...I wish I wasn't like this. \nEveryone always tells me I'm a big\nscaredy-cat.
Plus, no matter how much I practice,\nI always mess up when I get on stage.
I KNOW I'm better than that but I can't ever\nmake it work which makes me even MORE\nsad and then...then...
I just wanna sing as pretty as Eliaaaaas!
Come now! You're still a brave girl for\ncoming here to protect me.
*sigh* In any case, everyone is safe.
And it looks like you've got these fiends\nhandled, so...yeah! Keep it up, I guess.
Don't you think Pia should return to the\nthe choir about now?
*sniffle* Oh, no! It's soooo late!\nPractice is gonna start without me!
That kid can practice singin' all she wants;\nher attitude needs the real work.
Oh, I don't know. I think she showed\nbravery in her own way.

Anyway, we have to drive the rest
of these fiends off so the recital
can continue. I know everyone's
looking forward to it.
Pffft. Not that Elias kid. He looked like\nhe'd swallowed a lemon last time we\nsaw him.
Eh, that's no big deal. Kid's just gettin'\nto be at that rebellious age is all.
Heh. You might be right, Ranzal.\nAnyway, let's get back to it.
Hmm... I doubt the answer to Elias'\nrecent attitude is quite so simple...
Now then! Attend to me, everyone,\nand our practice can finally begin.\nListen carefully as I sing this note....
Now all of you try it.
You. Is there something troubling you?
A singing voice reveals its owner's true\nfeelings, and yours is currently trembling\nwith unease.
I've never heard anyone scold Elias\nlike that before.
That's quite enough chattering! Now then,\nfrom where we left off. And a-one...
Geez, Elias... What's going on with you...?
(I can't believe Lucretia scolded me in\nfront of everyone... This wouldn't be a\nproblem if my voice wasn't being weird!)
Oh, who am I kidding? I'll never be able to\nsing the way she does.
Y-you're the thing I heard in my dream!
Wh-what the heck ARE you?\nWhat do you want?!
I don't want to become an adult so...\nIT HAS TO GO AWAY!
You said that in my dream, but that's not\nwhat I want!
The darkness in your heart...\nThe power of darkness...
Stop it! Stay away from me!
THE POWER OF DARKNESS! I WANT IT!
Um...ha? Ha ha ha! Oh man, that was one\ncrazy dream! Hooo...
Is it just me, or are these chumps actually\neven stronger now?!
It certainly feels that way.\nWhat in the world is going on?
If that's the case, I'm afraid there may be\nan even more powerful enemy waiting for\nus up ahead.
Keep your guards up, everyone—I think it's\ngoing to be a long night.
